  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Multisectoral Humanitarian Assistance for Vulnerable Populations Affected by the Ebola Virus Disease Epidemic and Population Movements in Eastern Democratic Republic of the Congo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOM aims to improve the living conditions of survivors of the 10th epidemic of Ebola Virus Disease, displaced populations, and host communities in the provinces of North Kivu, South Kivu, and Ituri, Democratic Republic of the Congo through a response in health; shelter; and water, sanitation, and hygiene. IOM is working in 18 priority health zones affected by the epidemic and in 4 health zones hosting the largest number of displaced people, including at points of entry.</narrative>
  </description>
